MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/client/src/store/useGameStore\.ts$
ADVISORY: |
  Zustand SYNC handler gotcha discovered while debugging Pulse reactions:

  When merging a server SYNC payload, DON'T use length-based equality to dedupe
  collection fields. Items can MUTATE without changing the collection length.

  WRONG (this discarded reaction updates):
    chatLog: nextChatLog.length === state.chatLog.length ? state.chatLog : nextChatLog,

  Reactions are stored as metadata on individual ChatMessage objects in chatLog.
  When a player reacts, the message object is updated in-place but chatLog.length
  doesn't change → the equality check returned `state.chatLog` (stale data, no
  reaction) and the UI never re-rendered.

  RIGHT (use stableRef for any field that can mutate without identity change):
    chatLog: stableRef(state.chatLog, nextChatLog),

  `stableRef(prev, next)` does deep equality and returns prev if they're equivalent
  (preserving reference for downstream memoization), or next otherwise.

  Rule: any store field that holds an array/object whose CONTENTS can change
  independently of its IDENTITY/LENGTH must use `stableRef`. This applies to
  chatLog, channels, roster, completedCartridges, dmStats, and any future field
  that carries server-mutable nested data.
